suddenly you who have written a reply get a message from what apparently looks like that company or whatever it is. you have won! you see that the sender is the same name as the page you commented in the comment field to, and the image is the same.
and the message says you have to hurry. often you get a deadline. and a link. there you are often asked to provide account details or other personal items. but often it's just a hoax.

How can you be safer in dealing with such? is the sender of the message a page, or a person? If there is a page you should go to the page where you originally left is the answer to the competition, and then check the page that sends you the message. most likely there are differences you will notice.

check the page that sent you the message. when was it created, it has posts from far back etc. is there a person who is "named" the same as since you left a comment on, this is something that should make the alarm bells ring.

was to renew his passport and ID card today, and was surprised that it was formulated as an "application". checked the law, and it seems that the legislature has a completely different idea of what the ID card is than most people (and security people). police justice

The legislature proposes to use access control to ID papers as a means of restricting people's freedom of movement. this is not how ID papers should work, they give people the opportunity to confirm who they are. this nonsense they are trying to make people identityless and helping no one.

if I or anyone else tries to travel wherever I want with fake ID papers, then I will not be stopped from doing so by missing national ID papers. This is a solid fallacy of the legislature. non-existence of an object cannot prove or be the basis of anything.

probably the whole soup comes from an idea that someone should be caught at border crossings because they lack ID papers. the problem is the expectation that I am a "nice boy", but if I do not get ID papers then I am a "bad boy" and do I play by the rules?

I have been to several projects that have the same misconception of how people behave. that is, the assumption that a "bad boy" will relate to rules set up for "kind boy", and very often with regard to identification and authentication.
frankly, it seems that both the passport law and the ID card law were written by someone who has been lost on the floor as a child with his head first.

passport is a travel document, while ID cards are tried to be used as travel documents in the eu, but because there is no border control, the need for travel documents has disappeared. this nonsense is used to pry the travel document backwards.
